I"i<p>I‚Äôve used Jekyll to create my website.  A lot of the heavy lifting was done by <a href="https://mademistakes.com/about/">Michael Rose</a> in the form of a Jekyll theme he created called Hpstr.</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://mademistakes.com/work/hpstr-jekyll-theme/">Hpstr</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Much respect.</p>

<p>But, setup was pretty painful for me.  I knew nothing about websites, let alone creating a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_web_page">static page website</a>. I‚Äôve decided to set my hand to journal a lot of the nuances I ran into.  Try to save someone some time.  Or, save myself some time when something goes wrong.</p>

<p>These articles will not be on CSS, JavaScript, or HTML.  After tinkering with computers for 20 years, I still suck at CSS and HTML‚Äìno, there are much better resources on the matter.</p>

<p>I actually recommend spending $30 on the following Udemy courses.  They are great courses and will get you everything you need to be competitive.</p>

